dden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xvg1665702743974.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xvg1665702743974.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xvg1665702743974.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xvg1665702743974\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xvg1665702743974__configuration_settingsuniface_servlet_479883\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface servlets run in the environment of the web application. Settings for the\n      Uniface servlets, the WRD and SRD, are stored in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span> file, which\n      is the configuration file of the web application.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xvg1665702743974__p_d147272e1_d147273e1_d147274e1\">The settings for the Uniface servlets are grouped in servlet configuration sections, one for each Uniface servlet. The <span class=\"ph filepath\">web.xml</span> file uses the following format to configure servlet settings:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">&lt;web-app&gt;\n&lt;servlet&gt;\n&lt;servlet-name&gt;<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletName</var>&lt;/servlet-name&gt;\n&lt;servlet-class&gt;<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletClass</var>&lt;/servlet-class&gt;\n&lt;init-param&gt;\n&lt;param-name&gt;<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletSetting</var>&lt;param-name&gt;\n&lt;param-value&gt;<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletSettingValue</var>&lt;param-value&gt;\n&lt;/init-param&gt;\n...\n&lt;/servlet&gt;\n&lt;/web-app&gt;\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xvg1665702743974__p_d147275e1_d147276e1_d147277e1\">where:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xvg1665702743974__li_d51146e1_d51147e1_d51148e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletName</var>—name of the servlet (for example the Uniface servlet <code class=\"ph codeph\">wrd</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">srd</code>)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xvg1665702743974__li_d51149e1_d51150e1_d51151e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletClass</var>—Java class inplementing the servlet\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xvg1665702743974__li_d51152e1_d51153e1_d51154e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletSetting</var>—name of the servlet setting\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xvg1665702743974__li_d51155e1_d51156e1_d51157e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ServletSettingValue</var>—value of the servlet setting\n </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kfx1665702755236.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Java Servlets</a><p>The Java™ Servlet API is a standard extension to Java that extends the functionality of a web server. Java servlets run as Java EE (Enterprise Edition) web containers within a Java EE-compliant web server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ctl1665702541086.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Request Dispatcher (WRD)</a><p>The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) is used to deploy Uniface web applications. It is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering requests and maintaining connections between web servers and the Uniface Router. The WRD communicates with the Uniface Server via the Uniface Router.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rnm1665702667413.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD)</a><p>The Uniface SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering SOAP and WSDL requests for web services.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533940\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533940\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configuration Settings: Uniface Servlet Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface servlets run in the environment of the web application. Settings for the Uniface servlets, the WRD and SRD, are stored in the web.xml file, which is the configuration file of the web application. The settings for the Uniface servlets are grouped in servlet configuration sections, one for each Uniface servlet. The web.xml file uses the following format to configure servlet settings: <web-app> <servlet> <servlet-name> ServletName </servlet-name> <servlet-class> ServletClass </servlet-class> <init-param> <param-name> ServletSetting <param-name> <param-value> ServletSettingValue <param-value> </init-param> ... </servlet> </web-app> Copy where: ServletName —name of the servlet (for example the Uniface servlet wrd or srd ) ServletClass —Java class inplementing the servlet ServletSetting —name of the servlet setting ServletSettingValue —value of the servlet setting Related Links Java Servlets The Java™ Servlet API is a standard extension to Java that extends the functionality of a web server. Java servlets run as Java EE (Enterprise Edition) web containers within a Java EE-compliant web server. Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) is used to deploy Uniface web applications. It is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering requests and maintaining connections between web servers and the Uniface Router. The WRD communicates with the Uniface Server via the Uniface Router. SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) The Uniface SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering SOAP and WSDL requests for web services. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}